dev.b3nedikt.restring

Interface StringRepository

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    MutableStringRepository
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CachedStringRepository, MemoryStringsRepository, PersistentStringRepository, SharedPrefsStringRepository

    public StringRepository

    Immutable repository of strings resources. Restring supports all 3 types of string resources: strings, quantityStrings & stringArrays.

    See Also:
    strings, quantityStrings, stringArrays

    • Constructor Detail

      • StringRepository

        public StringRepository()

    • Method Detail

      • getSupportedLocales

        @NotNull
java.util.Set<java.util.Locale> getSupportedLocales()

        The Locales supported by the repository, Restring will only replace strings of Locales in this set. Meaning if strings contains a string resource, but this string resource does belong to a Locale not in the supportedLocales, it will get used by Restring.

        See Also:
        Locale, Locale, strings, Locale, supportedLocales

      • getStrings

        @NotNull
java.util.Map<java.util.Locale,java.util.Map> getStrings()

        The string resources with their Locale as key and maps of string resource names to their resource value as value.

        See Also:
        Locale

      • getQuantityStrings
